<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use stat cards to highlight key metrics at a glance</li>
    <li>Choose border colours that match the metric type (success for positive, danger for issues, etc.)</li>
    <li>Use appropriate icons that represent the metric</li>
    <li>Keep labels concise and uppercase for consistency</li>
    <li>Use large, bold numbers (h5) for the main value</li>
    <li>Include shadow for depth and visual separation</li>
    <li>Make cards clickable when they link to detailed views</li>
    <li>Use responsive grid layout (col-md-3, col-lg-3, etc.) for multiple cards</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Ensure sufficient colour contrast for all text</li>
    <li>If cards are clickable, use proper link semantics</li>
    <li>Include descriptive text labels, not just numbers</li>
    <li>Use semantic HTML structure</li>
    <li>Ensure icons are decorative (use <code>aria-hidden="true"</code>) or have appropriate alt text</li>
</ul>
